# Stay Safe Online: Prevention Checklist for College Students

## General Safety Tips

| # | Tip |
|---|-----|
| 1 | **Use Strong, Unique Passwords** — Create passwords with at least 12 characters combining uppercase, lowercase, numbers, and symbols. Use a password manager to store them securely. Never reuse passwords across multiple accounts. |
| 2 | **Enable Two-Factor Authentication (2FA)** — Activate 2FA on all important accounts including email, social media, and banking apps. Use an authenticator app (like Google Authenticator) rather than SMS where possible. |
| 3 | **Think Before You Click** — Never click on suspicious links or download attachments from unknown senders. Verify URLs carefully—cybercriminals often use misspelled domains (e.g., "amaz0n.com") to deceive you. |
| 4 | **Review Privacy Settings Regularly** — Set your social media profiles to private. Remove old posts, tags, and check-ins that reveal personal information like your location, daily routine, or college schedule. |
| 5 | **Log Out from Shared Devices** — Always log out of accounts when using college computer labs, library systems, or friends' devices. Never save passwords on public or shared computers. |
| 6 | **Keep Devices Updated** — Install operating system updates, app updates, and security patches promptly. These often contain fixes for recently discovered security vulnerabilities. |

## Financial/UPI Safety Tips

| # | Tip |
|---|-----|
| 7 | **Never Share UPI PIN, OTP, or Card Details** — Legitimate organizations will never ask for your UPI PIN, OTP, or debit/credit card details over phone, email, or SMS. Treat any such request as a scam immediately. |
| 8 | **Verify Payment Links Before Transacting** — Only use trusted apps like Google Pay, PhonePe, or your bank's official app. Avoid clicking on payment links received via WhatsApp or email. Check the UPI ID carefully before confirming any transaction. |

## Reporting Channels

If you or someone you know becomes a victim of cybercrime:

| Channel | Details |
|---------|--------|
| **National Cyber Crime Reporting Portal** | cybercrime.gov.in — File a complaint online, including anonymous reports for cyberbullying cases |
| **Cyber Helpline** | 1930 — 24x7 toll-free helpline for immediate assistance and reporting |

> **Remember:** In case of financial fraud, report within 10 minutes for the best chance of recovering money through the "Report and Recover" feature on the portal.
